[{'created': '2014-06-17 18:43:45.000000000', 'message': "Cut the heat flavor

1024Mb memory is too much for single instance.
approximately 4 GiB memory used even without a booted VM.

The heat auto-scaling scenario needs to boot 3 VM
(currently disabled), if any other test running in parallel
and boots up a vm it would easily can cause OOM an
issue.

The heat-slow job can work with 128 MiB instance memory,
but this change reduces it just to 512 MiB (safer for the guest),
and enough to avoid OOM issues on the host,
and let us to heve more vm at the same time.

The m1.tiny flavor is not good because now it has a hard coded
1 GiB disk limit and the f20 image requires 2 GiB.
Setting the disk size to '0' -> automatically use the virtual size
of the image.

Using multiple cores does not really helps in boot time :(,
but it might cause higher host load. (More locking)
Reducing the core number to 1.

Change-Id: Ice7c1253d15e91fd1c02bc8c6809335aaebfff4a
(cherry picked from commit 51557a502550e5b672f1e2c7187e08d3ded91c99)
"}]
commit_message:
Cut the heat flavor

1024Mb memory is too much for single instance.
approximately 4 GiB memory used even without a booted VM.

The heat auto-scaling scenario needs to boot 3 VM
(currently disabled), if any other test running in parallel
and boots up a vm it would easily can cause OOM an
issue.

The heat-slow job can work with 128 MiB instance memory,
but this change reduces it just to 512 MiB (safer for the guest),
and enough to avoid OOM issues on the host,
and let us to heve more vm at the same time.

The m1.tiny flavor is not good because now it has a hard coded
1 GiB disk limit and the f20 image requires 2 GiB.
Setting the disk size to '0' -> automatically use the virtual size
of the image.

Using multiple cores does not really helps in boot time :(,
but it might cause higher host load. (More locking)
Reducing the core number to 1.

Change-Id: Ice7c1253d15e91fd1c02bc8c6809335aaebfff4a
(cherry picked from commit 51557a502550e5b672f1e2c7187e08d3ded91c99)

My main concern is the flavor creation. I'm not sure that this guide is the right place to document it. There's probably other solutions, and getting more opinions on this before making changes is probably a good idea :)

commit_message:
Added trove chapter to user guide

The user guide did not have a chapter on how to use trove.

This commit covers the first topic in the chapter,
how to create and access a database.

This commit is a partial implementation of the blueprint.

Change-Id: I3824ae796c0c1d4175ef9fe6edc8f1cbe8d300f8
blueprint: user-guide-trove-chapter

subject: Control update, delete for cisco-network-profile Add new behavior to control update and delete operations for the cisco-network-profile resource extension. The new behavior is to allow update and delete operations only if there are no neutron networks associated with a particular cisco-network-profile instance.

commit_message:
Control update, delete for cisco-network-profile
Add new behavior to control update and delete operations for the
cisco-network-profile resource extension.
The new behavior is to allow update and delete operations only if
there are no neutron networks associated with a particular
cisco-network-profile instance.

[{'created': '2014-06-18 07:29:01.000000000', 'message': "Big Switch ML2: sync detection in port-update

Adds logic to the update_port_postcommit method of the
Big Switch ML2 driver to detect when afailure to update
the port via REST was caused by the backend being out-of-sync
with neutron.

This was accomplished by checking for the NXNETWORK message
which indicates that a port request referenced a network that
does not exist on the backend. This only occurs when they are
out-of-sync so the driver will then trigger a full topology sync.

The same logic exists in the port creation method shared with
the Big Switch plugin. However, the Big Switch ML2 driver does
not send port requests to the controller unless the port binding
host ID is set, which doesn't occur until a port update after
binding in the ML2 scenario. Therefore, the logic has to be repeated
in the ML2 driver port update operation.

Closes-Bug: #1331335
Change-Id: Id6488fbdea2c8c22a34e775977d94389c8da74f8
"}]
commit_message:
Big Switch ML2: sync detection in port-update

Adds logic to the update_port_postcommit method of the
Big Switch ML2 driver to detect when afailure to update
the port via REST was caused by the backend being out-of-sync
with neutron.

This was accomplished by checking for the NXNETWORK message
which indicates that a port request referenced a network that
does not exist on the backend. This only occurs when they are
out-of-sync so the driver will then trigger a full topology sync.

The same logic exists in the port creation method shared with
the Big Switch plugin. However, the Big Switch ML2 driver does
not send port requests to the controller unless the port binding
host ID is set, which doesn't occur until a port update after
binding in the ML2 scenario. Therefore, the logic has to be repeated
in the ML2 driver port update operation.

Closes-Bug: #1331335
Change-Id: Id6488fbdea2c8c22a34e775977d94389c8da74f8

commit_message:
Isolated network support

This patch aims to enable support for both:
- isolated metadata which enable metadata support on isolated networks.
- metadata networks which allows for serving metadata requests coming
  from a dedicated metadata access network

Conflicts:
	manifests/agents/dhcp.pp
	spec/classes/neutron_agents_dhcp_spec.rb

Change-Id: I0e892c4183bd2bf1910b9b6758c1759475053529
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
(cherry picked from commit 8654569fb4c53f8648578f8485fad80e3fe69e52)

This is perfectly fine change which brings a good refactoring into the way we are handling state chagnes now. But it looks that original way we are handling identity transitions is somewhat strange.

What does the value returned by change_state means? Sometimes it is checked and InvalidState exception is raised when it's False, sometimes it's not even looked at. But the only case when it can return False in current master is when we are moving task from PENDING to PENDING, which is a perfectly fine thing to do (e. g. when we are resetting subflow to be retried after it was reverting).

So, in the first place, I see no reason for change_state methods to return anything but usual None.

So, what should we do when identity transition is requested? I think sometimes there are valid reasons to do so, so it should just work. We might opt to ignore the transition when state does not have result, as an optimization and to avoid unnecessary notifications, but otherwise this is perfectly fine transition, if our state machine allows it.

I proposed the change according to what I wrote above: https://review.openstack.org/100805"}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2014-06-18 17:49:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Thanks, that does seem like a better refactoring. I also found this change_state usage to be a little weird and not consistent (which is bad). Checking out that other review.'}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2014-06-18 17:54:49.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Concretely define & check identity transitions

To match how we declare what the static transitions are
for tasks and flows also add in a allowed group of atom
identity states and a validation function and use this to
avoid repeating the same logic in the action classes.

Change-Id: I2ffae5a67267d35f0f6e61fff3b022c21fc728ac

commit_message:
Correct node erase sequence

This sequence is more accurate as it sends SIGTERM to all processes.

- Send SIGTERM to all processes
- Trap SIGTERM
- Sync and set RO flag on all partitions
- Erase bootable partitions with dd
- Send "b" to sysrq-trigger

Closes-Bug: 1268641
Closes-Bug: 1279720

commit_message:
Adds CLI to package catalog

New CLI operations to manage the package catalog:
- package-list
- package-show
- package-delete
- package-download
- package-import

Package-import currently allows only to create a package out of a single hot template
Such packages will work only after I927af0e96f1613e8843ac47844e9c19fa00fdaa6 lands.
For Heat-imported templates a Heat logo will be added, which is now bundled.

Also changes the logging level to WARN and above, so the INFO-level messages
from underlying HTTP clients are not written to console

Change-Id: I9ba290ae14c8d5388b113e4ab7e38cf15c2e31cf
Targets-blueprint: murano-cli-client

commit_message:
Add token delete command for identity v2

Identity v2 has undocumented support for token delete and
keystoneclient also has support.

Change-Id: Ib98d17958ceb88f7b63471691dee71fdb884ce2e
Closes-Bug: #1318442

commit_message:
Adjust permissions

This changeset
- removes executable bits from README.md
- adds executable bits to shell scripts

These changes are largely symbolic, except for osbash.sh which users are
expected to run without having to change permissions or passing it as an
argument to bash.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I91cce85862171a360c31e1e7628a708dfefd70f1

commit_message:
Add labs artifacts to .gitignore

The training-labs scripts create various artifacts that should not be
tracked by git. They are created in four directories which are added
to .gitignore by this changeset.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I89b103216ca3993448948966b832886bdd7a0ccf

commit_message:
Fix host manager node detection logic

This is the last in a series of patches to prepare Ironic for the
removal of capabilities in Nova HostManager.

IronicHostManager used to rely on capabilities info to decide which
host state class to use, VM or baremetal. This has been broken since
host capabilities reporting were removed in Nova, resulting in Nova
HostState class always being used.

This patch fixes the detection logic in IronicHostManager to correctly
choose IronicHostState class for use with baremetal nodes. Tests are
added to verify that the correct class is used for both vm and
baremetal nodes.

In reality, the new detection logic will not start to deliver the
correct HostState class until the Nova HostManager change has landed.

Change-Id: Ifa47d721835cfea87e9d0bce87c7853dd6724b98
Closes-Bug: #1260265

commit_message:
Don't look for ISO image when only doing wbatch

The current code looks for the installation ISO (and downloads it if
the ISO is missing) even if the user requested that only Windows batch
scripts be written.

With this patch, osbash calls find_install-iso only if it was asked to
build a basedisk on the local machine.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I7af15dcd4fa99671a85a924b23f434303049fcd2

commit_message:
Enable token-cleanup for debian

Token cleanup cron job is enabled only for Fedora. This fix enables
for all the platforms

One other reason I chose the approach that I chose was to minimize the impact for those who are providing the correct content type.'}, {'account_id': 1091, 'date': '2014-06-12 16:32:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I agree both of these approaches does not impact if supported content-type header is provided.

I think one other approach could have been to generate 400 error if content-type is 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' where some message like "Supported content-Type header value is required". This will avoid special handling of specific content-type. Curl request always have the option of adding needed header. May be we can have white list of supported content-types. If too ambitious, may be its config driven instead of defining the list in code.'}, {'account_id': 9234, 'date': '2014-06-12 19:47:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I have abandoned my CR and started a blueprint for this one (see https://blueprints.launchpad.net/barbican/+spec/barbican-enforce-content-type).  Would you do the same?'}, {'account_id': 1091, 'date': '2014-06-18 17:04:11.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Abandoning as Steve has proposed a blueprint around this (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/100625) which will require clients to pass valid Content-Type header as part of request otherwise 415 error will be raised'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-11 16:28:12.000000000', 'message': "Adds hook for setting default content type

Sets content-type to 'application/json' if missing or uses client default which
is 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' for POST request.
This change is done via on_route hook which is executed before pecan routing
takes place.

Change-Id: I3e2508b0d4bac4d1b275f3b4584d9207e148ad9e
Closes-Bug: #1320276
"}, {'created': '2014-06-11 16:43:09.000000000', 'message': "Adds hook for setting default content type

Sets content-type to 'application/json' if missing or uses client default which
is 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' for POST request.

commit_message:
Adds hook for setting default content type

Sets content-type to 'application/json' if missing or uses client default which
is 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' for POST request.
This change is done via on_route hook which is executed before pecan routing
takes place.

Change-Id: I3e2508b0d4bac4d1b275f3b4584d9207e148ad9e
Closes-Bug: #1320276

Implement extend volume in NFS driver

This fix implements the extend_volume functionality in the NFS
driver.

commit_message:
Pin tests to rspec < 2.99

Pin to rspec < 2.99 until rspec-puppet officially supports rspec 3.x.
This is to avoid warnings due to deprecated matchers in the
rspec-puppet gem.

This patch also reverts the change of be_false to be_falsey that was
temporarily required for rspec 3 compability.

Partial-Bug: #1326034
Change-Id: I1f7a754cf285c598169059e757c1a905762e2ce0

commit_message:
Add uri in Plan yaml response

We now return the plan uri in the response of Plan on POST/PUT/GET methods,
so when the CLI does "solum app create plan.yaml" the uri field can be filled.

Closes-bug: #1331526
Change-Id: I86777c18010f356526656d13ce7798d092e0c815

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-13 14:40:49.000000000', 'message': 'Adapt keystone_endpoint for new upstream modules

New openstack modules (v4.0.0) use "${region}/${name}" as
"keystone_endpoint" resource name which is incompatible with old
"keystone" module. From the other hand, new upstream "keystone"
module (v4.0.0) is not compatible with old openstack modules.

This is a temporary workaround to support both old-style and new
"keystone_endpoint" names. It will allow us to use new modules
along with old ones during upstream synchronization process.

This workaround will be removed when we update "keystone" module
to the upstream 4.0.0 version.

Change-Id: Ib5c232599273f93b7806413316d35af176a21bb0
Implements: blueprint merge-openstack-puppet-modules
'}]
commit_message:
Adapt keystone_endpoint for new upstream modules

New openstack modules (v4.0.0) use "${region}/${name}" as
"keystone_endpoint" resource name which is incompatible with old
"keystone" module. From the other hand, new upstream "keystone"
module (v4.0.0) is not compatible with old openstack modules.

This is a temporary workaround to support both old-style and new
"keystone_endpoint" names. It will allow us to use new modules
along with old ones during upstream synchronization process.

This workaround will be removed when we update "keystone" module
to the upstream 4.0.0 version.

Change-Id: Ib5c232599273f93b7806413316d35af176a21bb0
Implements: blueprint merge-openstack-puppet-modules

commit_message:
Pin gem versions for stable branch

This intends to pin all the major gems to the version they were during
development cycle.  This should isolate the existing tests from changes in
rspec, etc.

Change-Id: I13b82b73e805fb87ee95743130f1485abf3fc734

commit_message:
Prefix database parameters with database_ for consistency

Although database configurations were moved to the new database
section, parameters were not renamed accordingly.

This change renames those parameter for consistency with the other
modules and actual database configuration names.

Change-Id: I34855839963faa4c60f482df014b4986c7acab92

commit_message:
Add dhcrelay monitor via supervisor to restart

Dockerctl can start dhcrelay, but not ensure it
stays running. Supervisord can handle this task,
so it should watch the pid of dhcrelay and trigger
restart if it exits.

Change-Id: I75909d25418e625a2b154125e9a76e22c7443e47
Closes-Bug: #1324152
(cherry picked from commit acf69bd4c1441458843a59858038d11ad2bbe9cc)

commit_message:
Remove the device handling from pci device object

Remove the device handling code at pci device object to make
it similar to other NovaObject.

Remove some usage in test cases.

Closes-Bug: #1273852

Change-Id: I4487ae0b36de18365d12593f480c05f0fe726769

commit_message:
Use new pci device handling code in pci_manager

As we remove some pci device method from PCI device object,
update the pci manager accordingly.

Closes-Bug: #1273852

Change-Id: I0ec0e7b03625888a207918816b6e2d537b6d7d54

commit_message:
Pin gem versions for stable branch

This intends to pin all the major gems to the version they were during
development cycle.  This should isolate the existing tests from changes in
rspec, etc.

Change-Id: Iacf3a246adf1fc3ca1b5e42f0e0711cbfb1e1c9c

commit_message:
Added '' as a valid value for gateway_ip

If the gateway_ip attribute on neutron_subnet is set to an empty string
('') then it will trigger removing the DHCP gateway setting from the
subnet.  This is equivalent to the --no-gateway flag in the CLI.

Change-Id: Id4b74062d5b5b2fb335167af4e7cfcc32c4db703
(cherry picked from commit d202e4bbf70be6d7e70a87e5be334c0b69f3516c)

commit_message:
Pin gem versions for stable branch

This intends to pin all the major gems to the version they were during
development cycle.  This should isolate the existing tests from changes in
rspec, etc.

Change-Id: Ia50327632aeb76e1a9591ad5e9b3e6f49238fe3b

[{'created': '2014-06-05 19:30:54.000000000', 'message': 'Updated scenario tests to latest Tempest master

The __init__ method of the OfficialClientManager Tempest class changed
since we implemented our Tempest test. Now this method receives only one
parameter with all the credentials instead of three (user, password,
project). To fix this the ResourceReservationScenarioTest was modified
to use the new API. Also a not valid import was fixed and some minor
things of the test were fixed.

Change-Id: Ic79bdfb0e85d7a47310978a5c3ebd6a37195795e
Closes-Bug: #1326532
'}]
commit_message:
Updated scenario tests to latest Tempest master

The __init__ method of the OfficialClientManager Tempest class changed
since we implemented our Tempest test. Now this method receives only one
parameter with all the credentials instead of three (user, password,
project). To fix this the ResourceReservationScenarioTest was modified
to use the new API. Also a not valid import was fixed and some minor
things of the test were fixed.

Change-Id: Ic79bdfb0e85d7a47310978a5c3ebd6a37195795e
Closes-Bug: #1326532

commit_message:
Don't comment out the service_providers options

Disabling the neutron service providers was necessary during the
icehouse development cycle, but is not needed anymore.

Change-Id: I5a9a1632d34ab66e3e0192687e093f0ecbbf87d2
backport: icehouse
Closes-Bug: #1326856
(cherry picked from commit fbdc2f013eee1997c32171ab49193a2bb048a37c)

commit_message:
Make sure we call BaseTestCase.setUp() first

Some test cases instantiate RPC clients in setUp() before calling to
super(). After we port to oslo.messaging, we'll initialize RPC layer in
BaseTestCase, so we should make sure we call there before proceeding
with clients in subclasses.

blueprint oslo-messaging

Change-Id: I6fdcba0ba690c75d1a472b3ad050c21f5f53a1d0

commit_message:
Pin neutron gem versions for stable branch

This intends to pin all the major gems to the version they were during
development cycle.  This should isolate the existing tests from changes in
rspec, etc.

Partial-Bug: 1326034
Change-Id: I17ffd9255de6e04d0b036fa9466bf59171b1a762

commit_message:
Don't explicitly call .stop() on mock.patch objects

BaseTestCase already cleans up all mocks via .stopall(), so there is no
need to do it in each test case.

Change-Id: I7165ea9682a3dce3a76e90e309b763c939729d84

[{'created': '2014-06-03 14:01:38.000000000', 'message': "Don't instantiate RPC clients on import

In oslo.messaging port, we'll need to make sure no RPC clients or
servers or notifiers are created before RPC layer is initialized using
n_rpc.init(). This means that there should be no global objects that
create those objects on __init__.

There should also be no such class attributes because in that case
import will iself instantiate the object, probably before RPC layer is
ready.

blueprint oslo-messaging

commit_message:
Don't instantiate RPC clients on import

In oslo.messaging port, we'll need to make sure no RPC clients or
servers or notifiers are created before RPC layer is initialized using
n_rpc.init(). This means that there should be no global objects that
create those objects on __init__.

There should also be no such class attributes because in that case
import will itself instantiate the object, probably before RPC layer is
ready.

blueprint oslo-messaging

Change-Id: Ia8a9fd39777c75e4253f5518c2de6be551cc365b

commit_message:
Add XML deserializer for qos_manage delete_keys API

XML deserializer is missing for delete_keys API resulting XML format
request not being correctly handled by QoS Manage API extension. This
patch adds XML deserializer for the API.

Also add unittest for qos_manage XML serializer and deserilizer.

Change-Id: I7b3ac6822c52f11b08d767aa55b7107bd0333c36
Closes-bug: #1312553

commit_message:
auth_token _cache_get checks token expired

When auth_token stores the token in the cache, it's stored with
the expiration time; but when the token is retrieved from the
cache, if the expiration time has passed the token is treated as if
it wasn't cached. This creates extra work because now auth_token
has to check the token expiration (either by decrypting the PKI
token or online validation for UUID tokens).

With this change, getting the token from the cache will fail if the
expiration is past.

Change-Id: Id0ec6b3c2e5af4a2d910f16da4e0312733fc2198

commit_message:
Remove check_{attach,detach} from volumes API

These methods are not called from anywhere and are likely just a relic
from splitting Cinder out from Nova. Moreover their usage from the API
should really be discouraged as they are inherently racy (the result is
immediately outdated since it is not atomic with anything that might
follow).

Partial-bug: #1302774
Change-Id: I5d79b22b2a1d3c9be429a13d094328fc2075fcd2

commit_message:
Fix the notify method of the routing notifier

The notify method of the routing notifier don't have the correct
signature and change the case of the priority.

This change fixes it.

Change-Id: I833b19d0c054c94b861a4f6cc263c3487fa0e544
Closes-bug: #1316681

commit_message:
Require django-pyscss 1.0.1 for django-compressor 1.4 support

Since django-compressor 1.4 changed the parameters for its filter
class, we need a newer version of django-pyscss that takes that
change into consideration.

This is needed for patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/90371/

Change-Id: Ie2389fa60ee5c60689e55f193ebbbd57b1c9959d
Partial-implements: blueprint bootstrap-update

commit_message:
Fix pool statistics for lbaas reference haproxy driver

Active Connections and Total connections counters were mapped to
haproxy's active/total requests counters, which don't represent
connections, but HTTP requests. So in most low-load tests those
numbers stay 0

Patch maps connections API counters to haproxy session counters
and fixes unit test accordingly.

Change-Id: Ifc95d5cfc7fa654a560d9efa6ae81f1a058ef6b7
Closes-Bug: #1328784

commit_message:
Replaced names with  correct conf files

wrong config files were present earlier. Replaced
trove-api.conf with trove.conf and trove-taskmaster.conf
with trove-taskmanager.conf in all occurences

Fix a few typos in the shibboleth doc

- incorrect path /etc/shibboleth in an example
- authentication spelled incorrectly
- Shibboleth not capitalized once

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-17 06:48:41.000000000', 'message': 'Use known flavor ID as marker

The flavors marker test races with the flavors admin test because we
can list the flavors, pick the first flavor ID as a marker, then the
flavors admin test deletes that flavor and finally our attempt to list
flavors with that marker fails.

Avoid this by using a known flavor ID as our marker.

Change-Id: I56d043b58a403fc28a13b6f45540831ae8e0331d
Closes-Bug: #1330830
'}]
commit_message:
Use known flavor ID as marker

The flavors marker test races with the flavors admin test because we
can list the flavors, pick the first flavor ID as a marker, then the
flavors admin test deletes that flavor and finally our attempt to list
flavors with that marker fails.

Avoid this by using a known flavor ID as our marker.

Change-Id: I56d043b58a403fc28a13b6f45540831ae8e0331d
Closes-Bug: #1330830

commit_message:
Update docs template

To make things more consistent across all openstack projects, the
developer docs should be upgraded to the newer template used by
keystone and keystoneclient (and other projects).

I dropped in the necessary static files and themes, and updated
the config file to make the changes at build time.

Change-Id: I5a268cff3cd5af29ad712705d540b9d1d6667d56
Partial-Bug: #1331304

commit_message:
Removed OBJECT_FILENAME in swift list container

Removed OBJECT_FILENAME in swift list container command.To
list the objects in a container, command was "swift list
CONTAINER OBJECT_FILENAME", but the correct command is
"swift list CONTAINER"

Closes-Bug: #1330838

commit_message:
Fix wrong description of port status

When listing ports or showing port, the port status in response body
should be ACTIVE or DOWN.
Updated admin_state_up parameter to show a consistent
description.

Change-Id: Ie77531be7f13808f3e7d7d90cb0b731458f6bd94
Closes-Bug: #1330768

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 8874, 'date': '2014-06-09 03:43:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

(2 comments)

To Duncan Thomas:

1. The scene I mentioned does not mean that cinder-backup is down, and backup operation failed only because the db down for a short period.

2. Looking deep into the backup workflow and the secene:
1) check volume status
2) create backup item entry and set volume status and backup status---->{'volume': backing-up, 'backup': creating}
3) backup volume data and metadata to backup storage backend---->{'volume': backing-up, 'backup': creating}
4) First update volume status, and then update backup status. 
If db down just after update volume status to available, so backup status is stucked in creating. ---->{'volume': available, 'backup': creating}
If system administrator confirm backup operation failed in the step of update backup status, he/she
could change reset the backup status to available with backup reset state api without (1) restart cinder-backup
to change backup status to error and (2)delete backup and create backup again.

3. From cost/benifit/risk perspective, we could the benifit of introducing backup reset state api.
(1) assume:
     volume size & effect data 10G;
     min_backup_size: 2 ----almost the default size is 3
 (2) cost&benifit&risk:
    with reset-state api: 
        cost: 
            only need a db opertion
        benifit:
             very little write operation and less time
        risk:
           system administrator could locate the exact cause of prolems
    without  reset-state api:
        cost: too much write opertion and too much time
            restart cinder-backup
            delete backup: delete 20G data
            create backup: create 20G data
        benifit: NA
        risk: 
            restart cinder-backup while there are still backup/restore operation in progress"}, {'account_id': 8874, 'date': '2014-06-09 03:50:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

To yuzhou:
200 seems more suitable.'}, {'account_id': 8874, 'date': '2014-06-09 06:12:05.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-09 06:12:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Starting check jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-09 06:12:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Verified+1

Build succeeded.

- noop http://logs.openstack.org/16/98316/6/check/noop/df2bd32 : SUCCESS'}, {'account_id': 1207, 'date': '2014-06-10 08:22:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 8874, 'date': '2014-06-10 09:27:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

(1 comment)

1.Agree with your opinion.
Allowing "creating" -> "available" as a transition is very danger, we should add a constraint on reset backup state to "available".
Solution A: If we want to reset backup state a to "available" by calling reset backup api without flag '--yes-i-really-really-mean-it', cinder return an warning as follows:
    "Error EPERM: WARNING: this will change the bakcup status to *AVAILABLE*.
If you are *ABSOLUTELY CERTAIN* that the backup has been done finished in storage backend,
followed by --yes-i-really-really-mean-it."
If we want to reset backup state to "available" by calling reset backup api with flag '--yes-i-really-really-mean-it', cinder just change the backup status to "available". 
Solution B: We don't allow resetting bakcup state to "available". When we call reset backup state api to change backup status to "available", cinder just return an error 400.

How about your thoughts?

2. Add an use case for change backup status to error in next patch.'}, {'account_id': 4418, 'date': '2014-06-10 19:38:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

Made all the additional changes Tim made after the second round of review. The code(*arglist) solution for eval_builtin was particularly cool :). Jenkins passed. Didn't want to try git rebase since change id's were different, but following dependency chain of commit from this page up to three will show all changes in this branch."}, {'account_id': 11624, 'date': '2014-06-05 22:19:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

'Code' is stored in the Predicate during initialization as function pointers: 

class CongressBuiltinPred(object):

    def __init__(self, name, arglist, num_inputs, code):
        self.predname = name
        self.predargs = arglist
        self.num_inputs = num_inputs
        bfunc = 'f = ' + code
        exec(bfunc)
        self.code = eval('f')"}, {'account_id': 11624, 'date': '2014-06-18 15:26:20.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

old abandon change'}]

commit_message:
Add blueprint to remove translation of debug msgs

This spec proposes the blueprint to remove translation
of debug messages from Cinder to match up with what is
being done by other projects and to reduce the load on
translators.

Change-Id: Ic8320cca438ab09396f7d7563ce708ab5a30a5c0
blueprint: debug-translation-removal

commit_message:
Make storage.utils.keyify py3k compatible

In the storage.utils.keyify function, there is proxy object, that wraps
each item and makes it comparable via __cmp__ function. Since Python 3
old-fashion `cmp` is totally removed and only rich comparison functions
should be used (i.e. __lt__, __gt__).

Partially-implements: blueprint py3k-support
Change-Id: I36841fa33c7e49b8b14fb623d6859077e3d8b6f5

commit_message:
Increase the count of ping probes

It's allowed now to get at least 3 answers for no more than 10 requests.
Interval between connectivity checks is increaced (30 -> 60 sec).

Closes-Bug: #1322102

Change-Id: I0b227e3426c3d8b453986e6545829a11e125ce0b

commit_message:
Sharing codes for cinder v1 and v2 tests

Tempest doesn't have enough Cinder v2 api tests. We need to add more
tests for it. Cinder v2 api only has some small updates, so v1 and v2
tests could share service client and test code.
This patch makes the follwoing initial chanages to support sharing
codes between v1 and v2:

1. Rename volumes v1 client to a base client, then create v1 and v2
   clients inheriting base client.
2. Create common base test class instead of
   BaseVolumeV1Test/BaseVolumeV2Test. They will be remove after all
   test classes using sharing codes.

Partially implements: blueprint cinder-v2-api-tests

commit_message:
Don't include boto tests as part of smoke tests

Tests with the smoke attribute are used all over when we want to run a
subset of tempest. The smoke job is supposed to be a subset that gives
us the most bang for the buck in functional test validation. The ec2 api
falls outside of that being a third party api its always going to be
extra.

Change-Id: I474ada06064d2b236f52e623f7bc19326e711977

commit_message:
Sync versionutils from oslo-incubator

This is needed for comparing client versions from the command line to
required versions for CLI tests.

Tempest already has the immediate oslo dependencies of gettextutils and
log and those are up-to-date enough for what's needed in versionutils,
so this is a --nodeps sync.

Part of blueprint minversion-check-for-cli-tests

Change-Id: I19784499a9bb1135a9c8dc8b26fc56c53489ed22

subject: Remove unused oslo module and adjust opentstack-common.conf

commit_message:
Remove unused oslo module and adjust opentstack-common.conf

The issues are detected by new change about update.py
in I68c0108304be8a315bcefe939c22019caab9bc98. This patch
doesn't depend the oslo-incubator patch.
 * remove unused module crypto
 * add missing module loopingcall in openstack-common.conf
 * sort the modules in openstack-common.conf

Change-Id: I9f0fcd3803f89a6902f92d0ea691b9ae0235f64c

commit_message:
Fix hacking 0.9.x issues

Fixed issues:
H202 assertRaises Exception too broad
H305 imports not grouped correctly
H307 like imports should be grouped together
H405 multi line docstring summary not separated with an empty line
H904 Wrap long lines in parentheses instead of a backslash
E122 continuation line missing indentation or outdented
E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent
E131 continuation line unaligned for hanging indent
E251 unexpected spaces around keyword / parameter equals
E265 block comment should start with '# '

Change-Id: Ia2b8994c58686e3570f303f0725a2850d6b36e47

commit_message:
Edited the Orchestration module sections

1. Reordered instructions in the orchestration module installation section
    1. Create database.
    2. Create identity service credentials.
    3. Install packages.
    4. Configure service.
    5. Synchronize database.
    6. Start or restart service.
2. Edited titles and wording for consistency and conventions

Change-Id: I7f35274b7cbc99ce0452f4ec5b81d8412ea85b05
Implements: blueprint installation-guide-improvements
Co-Authored-By: Matt Kassawara <mkassawara@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Make deleting transient clusters safe

We want Sahara to be able to run distributed. I.e. several sahara-api
and sahara-engine should run in parallel and the whole setup should
work fine. For that to work we need to make deleting periodic clusters
safe, since a cluster could be deleted by two engines simultaneously.

Partially Implements: blueprint scalable-savanna
Change-Id: I33f9813ba58a4cca7d0221f518c29f8e605cc999

commit_message:
Fix errors in stop-services from missing includes

Current grenade logs show

---
Shutting down base
 ./lib/keystone: line 85: is_ssl_enabled_service: command not found
 ./lib/neutron: line 209: /lib/neutron_plugins/ml2: No such file or directory
 ./lib/neutron: line 215: /lib/neutron_plugins/services/loadbalancer: No such file or directory
 ./lib/neutron: line 221: /lib/neutron_plugins/services/metering: No such file or directory
 ./lib/neutron: line 226: /lib/neutron_plugins/services/vpn: No such file or directory
 ./lib/neutron: line 230: /lib/neutron_plugins/services/firewall: No such file or directory
 ./lib/neutron: line 233: has_neutron_plugin_security_group: command not found
 ./lib/neutron: line 946: /lib/neutron_thirdparty/*: No such file or directory
---

Sourcing the tls include should fix is_ssl_enabled_service missing,
and setting TOP_DIR for the neutron file should allow it to find the
plugin script

Change-Id: I1d1c2744d497ec8ea790d95642469069028bc3b4

commit_message:
Fix find_resource for keystone and cinder

The find_resource method had two hacks in in to support cinder
and keystone and I have removed those in favor of a monkey patch
for cinder.

The find_resource method used to attempt to UUID parse the id, but
it would do a manager.get anyway.  I changed it to skip the UUID
parsing.  This will make things run minorly faster and it supports
LDAP for keystone.

The find_resource used to attempt to use display_name=name_or_id
when finding.  This was a hack for cinder support, but it breaks
keystone because keystone totally messes up with the bogus filter
and keystone refuses to fix it.

Change-Id: I66e45a6341f704900f1d5321a0e70eac3d051665
Closes-Bug: #1306699

commit_message:
Make sure msgpack-python version >= 0.4.0

Now Marconi is using on msgpack and relaying on a new feature
introdcued in msgpack since 0.4.0. If user are using the version
under that, they may run into HTTP 503 code for some operations.

Change-Id: Ib24318c3d593f3d2d0625d0f2c582e26d81f43d1
Closes-Bug: 1331280

commit_message:
Make sure pymongo version >= 2.5

Now Marconi is exposing pymongo's cert options to user for the
maxium security, which was added since version 2.5

Change-Id: I504112d1f39e5a1b74bcae56b4b855c25b47acd8
Closes-Bug: #1328720

commit_message:
Sync up oslo log module

Main changes:
* removed annoying warning about RFCSysLogHandler.super
* improved password screening
* default log level for oslo.messaging

Closes-Bug: #1306559
Change-Id: I65ebf85e648cd5a1388ea77f6036d1f79f5b335b

in image-api should be 204. Replaced the earlier
Json response 200 with 204.

commit_message:
Added instructions for Havana to Icehouse upgrade on RHEL

I added instructions for the Havana to Icehouse upgrade process on
RHEL and derivatives such as CentOS and Scientific Linux. I also
addressed some issues in the equivalent instructions for Ubuntu.
Updated formatting for commands, file names, file extensions,
options, and a few other items.
Removed future tense where appropriate.
Updated book titles to actual names and surrounded with
<citetitle> tags.

Change-Id: I538e4e6d20ce11c95d4f60ae8f432f2eee20fcec
Closes-Bug: #1328987
Closes-Bug: #1328712

commit_message:
Admin guide updates

More changes to match the Admin Guide with the Icehouse GUI.
Also cleaning up some wording and other editing stuff.
Relatively small changes to smallish files, for the most part.

...and some niceness fixes that I thought I'd gotten earlier.

Added Diane's fixes

[{'created': '2014-03-31 15:41:16.000000000', 'message': 'Added use of trusts to Physical Host plugin

Now the physical host plugin uses trusts to communicate with Nova.

Added a decorator in order to create a trust in certain API calls.
Added the trust_id to the ComputeHost model. Added a DB migration for
this change and a unit test for it.
Added the MissingTrustId exception, which is raised when no trust_id is
provided to some methods of the RPC API.
Removed all the configuration keys related to the admin Climate user.
Modified NovaClientWrapper in order to use the information stored in
context.

Change-Id: I0b83a933c0d72871654f3c6252be5d5e2c4cfd54

commit_message:
Added use of trusts to Physical Host plugin

Now the physical host plugin uses trusts to communicate with Nova.

Added a decorator in order to create a trust in certain API calls.
Added the trust_id to the ComputeHost model. Added a DB migration for
this change and a unit test for it.
Added the MissingTrustId exception, which is raised when no trust_id is
provided to some methods of the RPC API.
Removed all the configuration keys related to the admin Climate user.
Modified NovaClientWrapper in order to use the information stored in
context.

Change-Id: I0b83a933c0d72871654f3c6252be5d5e2c4cfd54
Closes-Bug: #1285585

commit_message:
Bump hacking to 0.9.x series

In order to keep this patch to just a requirements bump, ignore new and
stricter hacking rules that are being triggered. Fixing up the code and
turning these on is out of scope of this patch and is for future patches.

Change-Id: I2eff542897a800457dedb7fb3fbea5283c5165ca

Add $TOP_DIR to the path when calling tools' scripts

The missing reference to $TOP_DIR prevent us to run stack.sh from a different
directory.

Cherry-pick of dae115251828e035fcad229f9c9d78856fb867b7

[{'created': '2014-06-16 17:10:29.000000000', 'message': 'Fix pool statistics for LBaaS Haproxy driver

Total connections was mapped to none of the counters
of haproxy. Active connections was mapped to active request
counter(qcur)) of haproxy which in low load situations
always remains zero.

Patch maps connections API counters to haproxy session counters
and fixes unit test accordingly.

Change-Id: I0ef4f76a75340232eb11a9b95453769ecd89d13a
Closes-Bug: #1319361
'}]
commit_message:
Fix pool statistics for LBaaS Haproxy driver

Total connections was mapped to none of the counters
of haproxy. Active connections was mapped to active request
counter(qcur)) of haproxy which in low load situations
always remains zero.

Patch maps connections API counters to haproxy session counters
and fixes unit test accordingly.

Change-Id: I0ef4f76a75340232eb11a9b95453769ecd89d13a
Closes-Bug: #1319361

Just like all other OpenStack projects use the hacking version from
test-requirements. Also install all dependencies before running flake8
so we can do import analysis such has H302. Turn off H302 until the
existing are resolved.

Change-Id: I6c5a983025406c1ebd4b537b95c6e8ce97849898
'}]
commit_message:
Use hacking from test-requirements

Just like all other OpenStack projects use the hacking version from
test-requirements. Also install all dependencies before running flake8
so we can do import analysis such has H302. Turn off H302 until the
existing are resolved.

Change-Id: I6c5a983025406c1ebd4b537b95c6e8ce97849898

commit_message:
Update Rally gates to support VM scenarios

Add "extra" directory for rally scenarios in gates. All files
from this directory will be copy pasted so we will be able to use
them in gates, because the path will be determined.

Also, print information about test environnement like available
services, flavors, images, networks, security groups and keypairs.

Change-Id: I19dd861beb11fb7ffdcf353f69759d841e7e8a01

Is the intent to set the same request_id for every client API call heat makes too?'}, {'account_id': 8844, 'date': '2014-06-10 05:16:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

Hi Steve, thank you for comment and +2!

I didn't think that far. This change just aims to efficient trace between heat and heat caller. But your idea might be good solution for preventing duplicate resource creation.
The appropriate key is depend on underlying side mechanism and that isn't clear now.
We should consider after that is clear."}, {'account_id': 7385, 'date': '2014-06-10 08:52:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 8328, 'date': '2014-06-10 20:35:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

I think idempotency is very important but is distinct from having correlators for tracing.  For example, health maintenance can lead to the maintenance agent issuing a request on its own, not in direct response to a request from one of its clients.  There may even be retries.  There may even have been an original request that DID originate with some other client. commit_message:
Support x-openstack-request-id for Heat

This patch aims to support "x-openstack-request-id" for Heat.

Nova, Cinder and Neutron have realized "x-openstack-request-id" functionality
by using oslo-incubator.middleware. This functionality will enable effective
log tracing between Heat and Heat caller.

Change-Id: Ida2f3d33b02557c2117aade27ccac7d9351886c9
Closes-bug: #1324065

work.

This patch defines the last missing dependencies between the different
parts that make up a RADOS cluster.

The entire module should now have sane dependencies and except where
explicitely wanted, the integration tests should not need to specify
them anymore and have been updated appropriately.

Here is an overview of the dependencies:

When installing:
* packages:
  * need the repositories
* configuration (ceph_config):
  * needs the packages, so the base folder exists
* ceph::mon:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
* ceph::keys:
  * needs the binaries (package)
  * if injecting needs the monitor to be available
* ceph::osd:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
  * needs monitors in the same cluster to be running
  * needs keys in the same cluster to be installed
* ceph::pool:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
  * needs monitors to be running
  * needs keys to be installed

When removing:
* ceph::mon:
  * needs the binaries (package) still around
* ceph::osd:
  * needs the monitors in the same cluster to still be available
* ceph::pool:
  * needs the monitors to still be available

Change-Id: I26933fcccdb4d953725070dc46456c36f2fee101

commit_message:
Configuring all dependencies in the manifests

This patch defines the last missing dependencies between the different
parts that make up a RADOS cluster.

The entire module should now have sane dependencies and except where
explicitely wanted, the integration tests should not need to specify
them anymore and have been updated appropriately.

Here is an overview of the dependencies:

When installing:
* packages:
  * need the repositories
* configuration (ceph_config):
  * needs the packages, so the base folder exists
* ceph::mon:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
* ceph::key:
  * needs the binaries (package)
  * if injecting configuration needs to be available (to find the
    address of the monitor)
  * if injecting needs the monitor to be available
* ceph::osd:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
  * needs monitors in the same cluster to be running
  * needs keys in the same cluster to be installed
* ceph::pool:
  * needs all configuration (ceph_config) to be done
  * needs monitors to be running
  * needs keys to be installed

When removing:
* ceph::mon:
  * needs the binaries (package) still around
* ceph::osd:
  * needs the monitors in the same cluster to still be available
* ceph::pool:
  * needs the monitors to still be available

Change-Id: I26933fcccdb4d953725070dc46456c36f2fee101

commit_message:
Use imfile for HAproxy remote logs delivery

The HAproxy is isolated in its own namespace and we cannot
send its logs to the remote syslog server via TCP sessions.
So, we have to use rsyslog imfile feature instead.

Closes-bug: #1330948

Change-Id: Ia36dafd3fde651b1a34fa5ca24e627054f8d1175
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Enable E251,E265 rules ignore H402

After bumping the hacking version to the 0.9.x series ignores were
added for several rules. This commit fixes the violations for a subset
of these rules and re-enables the checks.

Change-Id: If2445c395d481f3c5f6426a471da4ec8afb553f0

commit_message:
Fixes session timeout string in horizon

This bug fixes the session timeout string problem which
occurs when users clicks on the UI and Ui redirects the
user to the login page but without session timeout message.

Closes Bug: # 1231355

Change-Id: I307ff782c48a190cfbd6278705f45bcc8204dac0

commit_message:
Reenables the testr per test timeout

This change reenables the testr per test timeout, but set the value to
10 minutes, a gate job take 5-8 minutes, so test should not take more
than 10 minutes.

Change-Id: Ifccef9040529ec1a0b21076ed17d91a4f9737096

Add sanity tests for profiler and hmac usage

Create a few sanity test cases that validate that
the hmac and profiler integration work as expected
when invalid, fake and valid usage occurs.

This is the second in a series of patches to prepare Ironic for the
removal of capabilities in Nova HostManager.

host state class to use, VM or baremetal. This has been broken since

commit_message:
Add missing stats to IronicNodeState

This is the second in a series of patches to prepare Ironic for the
removal of capabilities in Nova HostManager.

IronicHostManager used to rely on capabilities info to decide which
host state class to use, VM or baremetal. This has been broken since
host capabilities reporting were removed in Nova, resulting in Nova
HostState class always being used.

Before IronicNodeState class can be used again, it must be updated to
store host stats as this is needed by ComputeCapabilitiesFilter to
correctly filter hosts or this filter will return no hosts.

Change-Id: I1661107883722bf14a488842373fd3027dc7a62c

"}, {'account_id': 1894, 'date': '2014-04-10 00:46:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

See the bug report, `configfile' is not substituted. I tested with a local.conf including [1], then I got the error [2]. I also tested with changing "touch" to "sudo touch" in merge_config_file() to find out what file was going to be created, then I found the following file :

  $ ls /\$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE
  /$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE

If you runs ./stack.sh in a "clean" environment, sudo privilege is not necessary, but it colud be much safer to making files under /etc with sudo privilege. Currently, all config dirs are owned by $STACK_USER, so this is not necessary for now.

[1]
---------------------------------------------
[[post-config|/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE]]
[ml2]
tenant_network_types = vxlan
type_drivers = local,flat,vlan,gre,vxlan
mechanism_drivers = openvswitch
---------------------------------------------

[2]
---------------------------------------------
2014-04-03 19:23:48.181 | + read a
2014-04-03 19:23:48.182 | + for configfile in '$(get_meta_section_files $localfile $group)'
2014-04-03 19:23:48.184 | ++ dirname '/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE'
2014-04-03 19:23:48.186 | + [[ -d / ]]
2014-04-03 19:23:48.187 | + merge_config_file /opt/stack/devstack/local.conf post-config '/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE'
2014-04-03 19:23:48.189 | + local file=/opt/stack/devstack/local.conf
2014-04-03 19:23:48.191 | + local matchgroup=post-config
2014-04-03 19:23:48.192 | + local 'configfile=/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE'
2014-04-03 19:23:48.194 | + [[ -r /$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE ]]
2014-04-03 19:23:48.196 | + touch '/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE'
2014-04-03 19:23:48.198 | touch: cannot touch '/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE': Permission denied
2014-04-03 19:23:48.199 | + exit_trap
2014-04-03 19:23:48.201 | + local r=1
2014-04-03 19:23:48.203 | ++ jobs -p
2014-04-03 19:23:48.204 | + jobs=
2014-04-03 19:23:48.206 | + [[ -n '' ]]
2014-04-03 19:23:48.208 | + exit 1

commit_message:
Fix unsubstituted filename creation

Since merge_config_file() tries to create an unsubstituted config file,
stack.sh fails due to permission denied in the file creation when you
use '[[post-config|/$Q_PLUGIN_CONF_FILE]]' and the file does not exist.

This patch deletes unnecessary 'touch' command, because the file will
be made by 'iniset' function in the next command line with evaled
string from 'configfile'.

This patch also fixes merge_config_group() to use evaled 'configfile'
when it checks the directory of the config file exists.

Change-Id: I608847a34143b5c6a1708c180186dd88a32dd44b
Closes-bug: #1294213

commit_message:
Wait for OVS to reconfigure when creating PUBLIC_BRIDGE

The '--no-wait' flag will not wait for ovs-vswitchd to reconfigure after
changes have been made to the database. This causes a race condition as
the bridge may or may not be up when 'ip addr flush dev $PUBLIC_BRIDGE' is
called. This commit removes the '--no-wait' flag which is safe as the
openvswitch services are already started earlier in stack.sh

Change-Id: I73ef1b731295d03b0f064c5f786196284c3e39ce
Closes-bug: #1328962

[{'created': '2014-06-18 10:58:17.000000000', 'message': 'Add main script: osbash.sh

This changeset introduces osbash.sh, the front-end script. It is little
more than a wrapper around the libraries in lib.

It sources configuration files and libraries, parses options and
arguments, and calls library functions to get the work done.

If a VM cluster was built (rather than just a basedisk), it can
export an OVA package containing the cluster.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I2136f7bc9bd67d0d11e2a7a9519ac202ec1ad92f

commit_message:
Add main script: osbash.sh

This changeset introduces osbash.sh, the front-end script. It is little
more than a wrapper around the libraries in lib.

It sources configuration files and libraries, parses options and
arguments, and calls library functions to get the work done.

If a VM cluster was built (rather than just a basedisk), it can
export an OVA package containing the cluster.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I2136f7bc9bd67d0d11e2a7a9519ac202ec1ad92f

commit_message:
Update IronicHostManager tests to better match how code works

This is the first in a series of patches to prepare Ironic for the
removal of capabilities in Nova HostManager.

IronicHostManager used to rely on capabilities info to decide which
host state class to use, VM or baremetal. This has been broken since
host capabilities reporting were removed in Nova, resulting in Nova
HostState class always being used.

IronicBareMetal tests make use of an internal Nova HostManager variable
in a way that hides the fact that IronicNodeState class is no longer
used. This patch rewrites tests to better reflect how Ironic/Nova code
now works and prepares for further changes that needs to land in Ironic
before Nova HostManager capabilities can be removed.

Change-Id: I795eaed58f6587585d89366d8f1e521588866a58
Partial-Bug: #1260265

commit_message:
Add localrc configuration file

The localrc file is read by osbash/wbatch and a few guest-side scripts.
It can be used to override variables used by the scripts.

Most notably, this is the place to select the Linux distribution to use
for the base disk or the VM cluster.

All variables have default values; localrc may be left empty.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I38e305ac40eda062bda4433178b7aed3c9e8e694

  make upgrade           - create full upgrade

commit_message:
Fuel upgrades, add yaml files and temapltes to egg

Even if include_package_data is True
when we run pip install fuel_upgrade
it doesn't include *.yaml files and templates.
We need explicitly specify this files.

blueprint upgrade-to-5-1
Change-Id: I6a0508ab917e1c3adeb842ddc11a78d48936ff44

commit_message:
Set up keystone databases

This script sets up MySQL databases for keystone, glance, neutron, nova,
and cinder.

The script is just a sample implementation. Depending on how the
training-guides are structured, it may be better to have a function that
can be called in service-specific scripts to create the database they
need.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Iaeca8e637c53a6b91d12915c8855b5b53639afd1

I'm not sure which direction we want to go in. AFAIK in general we are moving towards stricter input validation as a goal, and this takes us in the other direction."}, {'account_id': 6167, 'date': '2014-06-18 09:20:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I investigated the reason of this patch:

http://logs.openstack.org/48/96548/1/gate/gate-tempest-dsvm-postgres-full/fa5c27d/logs

Basically Tempest does not pass length='' to os-getConsoleOutput API on API tests.

In the above log, there were two negative factors.

 * Timeout happened before this error(exceptions.BadRequest) happened.
 * To investigate the timeout reason, Tempest tried to get console log with length=None.
   But in Tempest, XML client converts None to '' internally, this error happened.

On os-getConsoleOutput API tests of Tempest, this error does not happen even if XML test
because Tempest passes the length explicitly.
This problem happens only if some other problem happens before on XML tests.
In addition, XML support has been already deprecated in Nova.
So in long term, this problem will not happen.

In such situation, I'm not sure we should relax API validation in Nova side right now.
How about changing Tempest side to skip getting console log when the other problem happened on XML tests?"}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-06-18 10:52:09.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Allow empty length field for os-getConsoleOutput

Treat the absence of length field and an empty field the same. Couple
of code paths in tempest end up with length='' on the wire especially
in error scenarios which may mask the real problem.

Change-Id: I56a7198264bc37ca80434ff5e4efafdf3b4b5a76
Closes-Bug: #1329563

commit_message:
Big Switch: Import DB module in unit test

Import the portbinding db module in the Big Switch base test case
so the table gets created before the test is run. Otherwise the
tests will fail when being run with testtools because the portbinding
db isn't normally imported until a function call from the Plugin.

Closes-Bug: #1331240
Change-Id: Icbd2248a0c013c142ccf9b302a1ffa15c5a4e5ae

commit_message:
Fix inheritance for ConfigurationParameterDeleted

Reasons:
 - ConfigurationParameterDeleted is not
   inherited from any of exception classes.

Changes:
 - inheritance was updated from object to TroveError

Change-Id: I1e476ff7547ffb8efcc7fc3a13312b0f16fc4392
Closes-Bug: #1328865

commit_message:
Completely object-ify the floating_ips_bulk V2 extension

This converts the floating_ips_bulk APIv2 extension from using
direct DB access to using the FloatingIP object.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: I5fa7637b5eb06a9be51d7638701d98e3e033d68d

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-16 23:46:56.000000000', 'message': "Add bulk create/destroy functionality to FloatingIP

This adds bulk create and destroy functionality to the FloatingIP
object, which in turn requires that the DB API return the list of
IPs that it created.

This also fixes a bug in the load routine for FloatingIP, which
would previously try to load at FixedIP object with id=None,
which doesn't make sense.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: Ie3c7a5e672fcdb3e0df3d0e46b905b237dcfa182
"}, {'created': '2014-06-17 15:01:20.000000000', 'message': "Add bulk create/destroy functionality to FloatingIP

commit_message:
Add bulk create/destroy functionality to FloatingIP

This adds bulk create and destroy functionality to the FloatingIP
object, which in turn requires that the DB API return the list of
IPs that it created.

This also fixes a bug in the load routine for FloatingIP, which
would previously try to load a FixedIP object with id=None,
which doesn't make sense.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: Ie3c7a5e672fcdb3e0df3d0e46b905b237dcfa182

commit_message:
Fix method mocked in a test

Mock `api_client.alarms.list` instead of `api_client.alarms` in the
tests/alarm/partition/test_coordination.py:TestCoordinate.test_assigned_alarms
method.

Closes-Bug: #1329701

I agree with @asalkeld that this should be in a separate repo. I am happy to make one, but I would first like us to do some housekeeping:

1) A blueprint for this that clearly outlines the intended use case(s).

2) One or more bug/task ticket(s) that detail the implementation details for each use case.

3) Discuss this with Ed Cranford and other members of the Trove team, who have insights from lessons learned about trove-guestagent.

Ideally, I'd like to defer the addition of the guest agent for as long as possible if it's possible to address the use cases using alternate means. The consumption of memory within the guest is an important one. We need to balance the cost of that reality with the benefit of the agent, and potentially design around that."}, {'account_id': 9537, 'date': '2014-06-12 09:26:40.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-12 09:26:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I already asked Ed some questions about trove guestagent on irc a few days ago. I will not hesitate to ask him for more if needed.

I pushed the review for the new repo https://review.openstack.org/#/c/99705/'}, {'account_id': 1375, 'date': '2014-06-12 18:42:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

I'd like to see how long we can go without a guestagent. Trove deliberately cuts off SSH access to instances, necessitating the guestagent on the machines. If we don't need to categorically shut off SSH to our instances, we can take advantage of it. Maybe we could write a run-once agent that just generates a key for paramiko and hands it back to us via rabbit or something?

If we do end up with a guestagent, I agree with Angus and think we could get away with a separate repo. Memory use is a concern, and it's probably worth the trade-off of managing a separate repo instead of dropping all of solum into a guestagent.

I can't find much fault with your skeleton code here, though!"}, {'account_id': 9537, 'date': '2014-06-13 08:09:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

I guess we can try with SSH first.

Ed, what was the reason for trove to cut off SSH access ?'}, {'account_id': 1375, 'date': '2014-06-13 15:31:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Mainly to reinforce that trove containers are built for just the one purpose. At least, that's about how I remember it.

I don't think ssh access is cut off from the management network, but it's honestly been a little while since I've spun up my trove environment."}, {'account_id': 9537, 'date': '2014-06-18 10:02:51.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Add skeleton of a solum-guestagent

In order to configure and interact with any guest vm managed by
solum, we need a guestagent running on those VMs.

This patch is a first step for solum-guestagent

Also made some changes to config files generation to allow multiple
config file
- /etc/solum/solum.conf for solum global configuration
- /etc/solum/solum-guestagent.conf for agent configuration

This code is inspired by trove-guestagent

Change-Id: I45559985d447598abcee1043e9af600e6314b422

commit_message:
OpenStack Patching: install repos/puppets

The fuel-upgrade script have to install new repos and puppet scripts
that will be used for openstack patching.

Implements blueprint upgrade-to-5-1
Closes-Bug: #1327198

Change-Id: I8f3f0ba2dc30670c4cade52411690357d0afb675

commit_message:
Rename shards to pool

Shard turned out to be a quite overloaded/confusing term to use here,
although correct. We decided to rename our shard feature to pool.

P.S: I swear I didn't use sed O.O

Change-Id: Ic54f29a4da7d7690c9c9210b74876b96f0ae0eac

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-18 08:57:54.000000000', 'message': 'MySQL: Installation and basic configuration

This script implements the section "Database -> Controller setup" of the
OpenStack install-guide for Icehouse/Ubuntu.

It installs the MySQL server package and the Python library, sets the
database root password as configured in the credentials config file,
and edits my.cnf as described in the manual. -- This part shows how
devstack functions can be used to edit configuration files.

Note that mysql_secure_installation (from the manual) is not called
because the option that made it work for unattended installs didn't make
it into the version of MySQL that is in Ubuntu 12.04 LTS.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I4d40b84a18d42572214137fb664ffb514fee6ef9
'}]
commit_message:
MySQL: Installation and basic configuration

This script implements the section "Database -> Controller setup" of the
OpenStack install-guide for Icehouse/Ubuntu.

It installs the MySQL server package and the Python library, sets the
database root password as configured in the credentials config file,
and edits my.cnf as described in the manual. -- This part shows how
devstack functions can be used to edit configuration files.

Note that mysql_secure_installation (from the manual) is not called
because the option that made it work for unattended installs didn't make
it into the version of MySQL that is in Ubuntu 12.04 LTS.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I4d40b84a18d42572214137fb664ffb514fee6ef9

commit_message:
Add using share-server backend details in Generic driver

Method setup_network returns server data:
 - instance_id
 - ip
 - authentication data
   (username, password, private key path)

Renamed method get_service_instance to set_up_service_instance.

Added method ensure_service_instance to check that
service instance is available.

Added setting up security group, keypair, network on
initialization.

Made editing smb config using sftp.

Implements bp implement-backend-details-in-drivers

Change-Id: I0d1544e7adb18d58254261ed9502303672a5b8fb

commit_message:
Add osbash helper scripts

This changeset adds two simple helper scripts.

base_fixups.sh is run on every basedisk while it is built. The script
can be used to fix whatever is necessary to make the basedisk work.
Right now, all it does is remove 70-persistent-net.rules which (if left
untouched) would result in a network interface order that would differ
from Vagrant's.

The second script is a trivial debug helper that does nothing but wait
for the removal of a file it creates in /tmp. When the file is removed,
execution continues.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Id75a89ced5dcf132e91e7426df15436de585a203

commit_message:
Splits mongo storage code base

Move methods and classes that just helper around pymongo into
mongo/utils.py

This a preparation work to have mongo helper method that can be shared
between alarm and metering storage driver.

Partial implements blueprint dedicated-alarm-database

Change-Id: Ib359ce4c69b1310577e0481a380d5438f08ed597

commit_message:
Do a better job of quietening the logs

We were overriding the "defaut_log_levels" option and losing
some useful options. This just extends the list instead of
overwriting it.

Also added:
- stevedore
- periodic debugs

Change-Id: Iacef411f896854751beb44488ed4b2a8a7268fa8

commit_message:
Allow router external IPs to be set and read

This is a specification is to allow tenants to read
the external IP addresses assigned to their router
and for admins to explicitly set the IP addresses
on a router.

blueprint specify-router-ext-ip

Change-Id: Ibeaed1280e6736ef3b5f00db871946ad9c1e6c22

Docs previously listed the "cloud-initramfs-tools" package as part of the simplest way to enable automatic root filesystem resizing on boot. That's just a source package, which you can't actually install. cloud-initramfs-growroot contains the actual hooks for the growroot action.

Change-Id: Iccedeffd92c90772c504affafac6c65a302240b2
Closes-Bug: #1331179
'}]
commit_message:
Fix the cloud-initramfs-growroot package name.

Docs previously listed the "cloud-initramfs-tools" package as part of the simplest way to enable automatic root filesystem resizing on boot. That's just a source package, which you can't actually install. cloud-initramfs-growroot contains the actual hooks for the growroot action.

Change-Id: Iccedeffd92c90772c504affafac6c65a302240b2
Closes-Bug: #1331179

commit_message:
Notify systemd when starting Neutron server

systemd is notified only when Neutron is started with multiple api
workers. This patch adds systemd.notify_once() call when starting
Neutron server with api_workers=0

Change-Id: I95581dc5dffde6168c68d9f04cf8bdfcdb773ba8
Closes-Bug: #1330532

commit_message:
Scripts to clean disk and shut down

This changeset adds two simple scripts: one fills the unused space
of the root disk with zeroes to allow for better compression of the
resulting disk image, the other shuts the computer down.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I2e80518733b0e1e17a59192c6e2522f423709551

commit_message:
Scripts to configure yum and upgrade system

The first script in this changeset configures yum to use a proxy (if
VM_PROXY is set) and adds the RDO repo.

The second script updates the packages installed in a yum-based system.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Iad42b6aad2bf48329cb2c3bb2bc7a1d698d9c608

This script can be used to enable access to osbash VMs using the same
ssh key that is used to for logging into Vagrant VMs.

If the script is run from a directory shared with the host, the
downloaded key will be cached.

Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs

'}]
commit_message:
Allow osbash to enable Vagrant ssh keys

This script can be used to enable access to osbash VMs using the same
ssh key that is used to for logging into Vagrant VMs.

If the script is run from a directory shared with the host, the
downloaded key will be cached.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Ia541e01cabd69f794ea79d8a318f490f518d28ef

Edit /etc/hosts

This script makes sure the hostname can be resolved through /etc/hosts
and adds names for all interfaces in the VM cluster.

commit_message:
Remove misc.as_bool as oslo provides an equivalent

There isn't a need to have a misc.as_bool function
anymore now that we have imported the oslo incubator
strutils module since that module provides a function
that does *nearly* the same thing.

Change-Id: I7afe141d5a37c50b0c926144743f9af71db95bbf

commit_message:
Denote that other projects can use this library

This library while made primarily for OpenStack is and
should not be limited to just being used by OpenStack
and our documentation should reflect this.

Change-Id: I9721adc062b27ab9e893b97e29cc34c6cb889308

and IIUC, the openstack-common.conf marks oslo.middleware as dependency module, then everytime we sync with oslo, the audit and notifier modules will come back too.'}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2014-06-11 04:38:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I just think it's beyond scope of bug. Also, the other middleware may be used by others.

You should also modify doc/source/conf.py so it's not excluding audit/notifier files anymore.

You can change it to module=middleware.xyz to selectively import specific files.

Of course you'll need to make a pretty long list:

Module=middleware.base
Module=middleware.request_id

Might be easier to just remove them and we'll track it to make sure it's not added again."}, {'account_id': 6676, 'date': '2014-06-11 08:03:40.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-11 08:03:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Clean up oslo.middleware.{audit,notifier}

After migrating to oslo.messaging, the oslo.middleware.notifier and
oslo.middleware.audit can no longer work, we should remove these code.

Change-Id: Ie848d9f356eec670bbeeafc83f9e704212b1d2e4
Closes-Bug: #1327084

commit_message:
Display Horizon version number in System Info page

This patch adds the Horizon version number at the bottom of System
Info page.

Change-Id: I81514d1c99a32cd8161a65535638c235c2cfc317
Closes-Bug: #1261431

commit_message:
Update: persist current template on change

After each resource is updated, persist the modified template to the
database so that any new resources will be accessible to API calls -
including signals to new WaitConditionHandles. This also ensures that if
the Heat engine dies completely during an update, the template in the
database will still be in a consistent state.

Change-Id: Ie6f234302cf72213d4b0e1f5b963cd8def422498
Closes-Bug: #1291905
Closes-Bug: #1206702
Closes-Bug: #1328342
Implements: partial-blueprint update-failure-recovery

commit_message:
Update template incrementally as resources change

As a stack update progresses, maintain the contents of the template so that
they represent the current running state of the stack, instead of only
switching over wholesale at the end, so that if a failure occurs our state
and the template stored will be consistent.

Change-Id: If79e8b1dc212c548cad92fdbc340d61f5650f9d4
Implements: partial-blueprint update-failure-recovery
Closes-Bug: #1330016

commit_message:
Allow raw templates to be updated in the DB

Note that although this raw_template_update_template() will get called at
least every time the stack changes state (so twice for each operation), the
performance cost is negligible: we use the context's session, so the get()
will just retrieve the session's cached object, and we don't issue the
write unless the template has actually changed.

Change-Id: I3f231b88d08ab31c275cb9fecbf2600456c793c3

commit_message:
Update: Keep a copy of the old template for rollback

To implement the blueprint update-failure-recovery we will need to modify
the current template as we change the stack. We'll need an unmodified copy
to roll back to in the event of failure, so base the previous stack on a
copy.

Change-Id: Ic06acd3c9a89312d1ad8922e26ab02bee4bafeb0

commit_message:
Verify list_instance_action attributes of Nova API

This patch adds the JSON schema for Nova V2 & V3 list_instance_actions
API response and validate the response with added JSON schema
to block the backward incompatibility change in the future.

The response body of list_instance_actions V2 API is below:

{
    "instanceActions": [
        {
            "action": "reboot",
            "instance_uuid": "b48316c5-71e8-45e4-9884-6c78055b9b13",
            "request_id": "req-3293a3f1-b44c-4609-b8d2-d81b105636b8",
            "user_id": "789",
            "project_id": "147",
            "start_time": "2012-12-05 00:00:00.000000",
            "message": ""
        }
    ]
}

The response body of list_instance_actions V3 API is below:

{
    "server_actions": [
        {
            "action": "reboot",
            "server_uuid": "b48316c5-71e8-45e4-9884-6c78055b9b13",
            "request_id": "req-3293a3f1-b44c-4609-b8d2-d81b105636b8",
            "user_id": "789",
            "project_id": "147",
            "start_time": "2012-12-05T00:00:00.000000",
            "message": ""
        }
    ]
}

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I81a21a4ec0522318fd20c3db3e534fdcea7b8715

commit_message:
Add strip size support to rbd driver

Rbd support strip size for volume, in general, we would like to think the
default value 4M is a proper for most of users.

In the ceph side, the proper value of rbd strip size can improve performance for
the special OSD backend.

Implements blueprint add-rbd-strip-size

Change-Id: I44d89681a78bd70d8c185e3da7d58f59e6076899

commit_message:
Handle remote driver not loaded situation

An error in our code could lead to remote being used by sahara-api.
Since remote is not available there, an exception will be thrown like
the one in bug #1325989. We should give user a hint that switching to
sahara-all might fix the issue.

Related-Bug: #1325989
Change-Id: I79a00c225b5fe8f98f413b9d88d223076f9b94c3

commit_message:
Configure apt and update index

This script configures apt to use a proxy (if VM_PROXY is set), adds the
ubuntu-cloud repo (release set by OPENSTACK_RELEASE) and updates the apt
index.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I6a426ee31746424a761fc8cd6d81723ac7740f04

This script upgrades the installed packages in an apt-based system.
After a kernel upgrade, the old kernel is removed (in order to save
space), and so are packages and package files that are no longer needed.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Iaadcebc424572787d3a2d77f6b19ab636d65ee58
'}]
commit_message:
Upgrade system via apt

This script upgrades the installed packages in an apt-based system.
After a kernel upgrade, the old kernel is removed (in order to save
space), and so are packages and package files that are no longer needed.

Partial-Bug: 1312764
Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: Iaadcebc424572787d3a2d77f6b19ab636d65ee58

commit_message:
Remove quota-class-* commands from v3 shell

Commit 1b15b23b0a629e00913a40c5def42e5ca887071c removed the
os-quota-class-sets v3 API from Nova in Icehouse.  This change removes
the corresponding client code.

Closes-Bug: #1331095

Change-Id: Iaa2f4063e0f671da5a54ff89d0f1c1780a2687c4

commit_message:
Don't try to publish from www directory

The training-guides tox.ini was inherited from openstack-manuals
which merges static content from its www directory into its
publish-docs folder.

training-guides doesn't have a www directory -- it shares the static
content with openstack-manuals (they both publish into the same web
root).

Trying to copy files from a non-existent directory results in failure
which in turn prevents training-guides from publishing its manual.

This patch removes from tox.ini the commands that try to copy the
content of the www directory.

Closes-Bug: 1312764
Change-Id: I43f56523a7fe59d2d9ea92cabfcb4e926e751f6d

commit_message:
Import eventlet in __init__.py

All of this is because if dnspython is present in your environment then
eventlet monkeypatches socket.getaddrinfo() with an implementation
which doesn't work for IPv6. To turn this off you need to set an
environment variable before you do the import.

Resolves bug 1164822.

Change-Id: I2382db7b3ac4a2d940e0c45dfe3d48f499de2f16

commit_message:
Move dashboard from python-mistralclient

Also:
- add license headers
- set up tox for flake8 checks and venv
- remove run_tests.sh, tools/ and other stuff we don't need at the moment
- add basic sphinx setup for later use

Change-Id: I0d34fb9fd0bfd351d20474da88715b30ff3c3d61

commit_message:
Add res_last_path to store last metadata of a resource

Add res_last_path='/var/cache/heat-cfntools/last_metadata_<resource>'
in Metadata.retrieve() function to store metadata of a resource.
Remove md5 check between current metadata and last metadata, json.load()
will organize json structure.

Change-Id: Ie0c31a748f0add3fcab6a579431a28b60051f601
Closes-Bug: #1205375
Partial-Bug: #1133049

commit_message:
Separate the PCI device object handling code

Currently the PCI device object includes several functions like
alloc/free/claim etc. However, the NovaObject should not be used
this way, and it makes the PCI device object really different
with other NovaObject implementations.

This patch duplicates the PCI device handling code as separated
functions. No logic changes but simply code copy. A later patch
will delete the code at PciDevice object.

Closes-Bug: #1273852

Change-Id: I2389d29218d8619998f8df973004af004e8b1b76

commit_message:
Fix doc for service list

If a service is enabled, the "disabled_reason" field in response
for /v2/.{tenant_id}./os-services/detail is null, however, currently
it's specified as "" in the doc, thus may be confusing to users.

This patch change the template and doc, it should not cause issue to
existing applications.

Change-Id: Ia71ec4c97a355bcc1a7b63e6107db77f80a5d843
Close-bug: 1328382

commit_message:
Add hook for network info update

This hook will allow deployers to register scripts that will
be called whenever an instance's network information is updated.
Scripts will be called with original arguments of the network
info update function call.

Implements: bp instance-network-info-hook

Change-Id: I56ff28d305cf8d9a67b37c45062256b3899f11dd

commit_message:
Enhance and test exception safety in hooks

This patch adds exception handling when calling pre and
post functions of hooks. Exceptions will be caught and
logged, but the hook chain and function call will be
allowed to proceed.

Partially implements: bp instance-network-info-hook

Change-Id: I45e76cd156c244ff57f77db103a9a579f14ad4f1
